                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/378</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-24T15:00:00+03:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 24, 12.54 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>513. Referring to my 401, September 14, 4 p.m., and 423 September 24, 7 p.m.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d99fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_67">pp. 67</ref> and <ref
                            target="#pg_70">70</ref>.</note> British financial expert arrived here
                    with one hundred million new rubles which proposes paying British soldiers and
                    for other necessary expenses. The government is in financial straits but I have
                    objected to their accepting such new rubles, if tendered, as I think it [they]
                    will be. What understanding, if any, have we on the subject? Have you any
                    instructions?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
